title: If You Die Before You Die
description:
pass me this chalice
father take me in your palace
this world is just madness
but they don't see that yet
sleeping beauty's so peaceful
as shes lays her in her casket
afraid to wake up but
the pain is just past tense
die before you die again
look that devil in the eye and then
angels soar and you can fly with them
sometimes you hit your head boy try again
cuz the world is stranger than you know
tied together with a thread if golden rope
that doesn't break or snap or fray buts holds together hope
so here we go


golden rays of light that shine
out his hands and into mine
the ego melts like ice in summer time
we are connected to the great  divine
let us pray for eyes so we can see
if there is a you or is me
it dont exist outside eternity
a master piece infused with masters peace

drink deep beloved
drink deep my darling
cuz sometimes the flying
just feels like your falling
as you come out this wilderness
in submission and willingness
i will toss all the bitterness
into the sea of forgetfulness 

I dont feel a thing
death where is the sting
I have tasted seen
something like a dream
the outside of the cup is dirty man
but the insides squeaky clean
the divine has touched my mind and Ip
no longer think bout suicide cuz i
eat the bread and drink wine of christ
when its time to die you'll just see me smile
